  "text": "The Firefox CSP enforcement infrastructure under dom/security/ consists of the following key files:\n\n1. **CSP Parser** — `dom/security/nsCSPParser.cpp` (header: `dom/security/nsCSPParser.h`): Defines and implements the `nsCSPParser` class, which tokenizes and parses raw CSP header strings into directive/source-list structures.\n\n2. **CSP Context** — `dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp` (header: `dom/security/nsCSPContext.h`): Implements the `nsCSPContext` class (which implements `nsIContentSecurityPolicy`). This is the main runtime object that holds all policies for a document, evaluates requests against them, and drives violation reporting via `SendReports()`, `SendReportsToEndpoints()`, `SendReportsToURIs()`, and `FireViolationEvent()`.\n\n3. **CSP Utilities / Violation Reporting** — `dom/security/nsCSPUtils.cpp` (header: `dom/security/nsCSPUtils.h`): Implements the CSP directive and source-list data model — `nsCSPBaseSrc`, `nsCSPHostSrc`, `nsCSPKeywordSrc`, `nsCSPNonceSrc`, `nsCSPHashSrc`, `nsCSPDirective`, `nsCSPScriptSrcDirective`, etc. — including the `permits()` logic used during evaluation and violation detection.\n\n4. **XPCOM Interface Header** — `dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl`: Declares the `nsIContentSecurityPolicy` XPCOM interface that `nsCSPContext` implements, defining the public API surface for querying and enforcing CSP from C++ and JavaScript.\n\n5. **Script-src inline script evaluation** — `dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp`: The method `nsCSPContext::GetAllowsInline()` (around line 637) performs the script-src evaluation for inline scripts, checking nonces, hashes, and `'unsafe-inline'` against all held policies. The directive model for script-src is declared as `nsCSPScriptSrcDirective` in `dom/security/nsCSPUtils.h`."
}

